The paper deals with revenue guarantees for auctions, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.EC). The use of a single posted price and the distribution of buyers' valuations suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The mention of welfare and revenue approximation suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT).
